{"slideshow_credits": null, "snippet": "A public school calendar accommodation to the Muslim community is a gesture of welcome &#8212; and a welcome gesture.", "abstract": "Editorial welcomes New York City's decision to add Muslim holidays of Eid al-Fitr and Eid al-Adha to its school calendar; calls move positive step for inclusion and diversity that will not result in loss of school days and will cut down on student absences, while also making Muslims feel welcome at time of global unrest and anti-Muslim bigotry; calls for city to next add Lunar New Year to holiday calendar.", "section_name": "Opinion", "print_page": "20", "document_type": "article", "byline": {"person": [], "organization": "THE EDITORIAL BOARD", "original": "By THE EDITORIAL BOARD", "contributor": ""}, "web_url": "http://www.nytimes.com/2015/03/07/opinion/holidays-that-reflect-new-yorks-students.html", "lead_paragraph": "A public school calendar accommodation to the Muslim community is a gesture of welcome &#8212; and a welcome gesture.", "headline": {"print_headline": "Holidays That Reflect New York\u2019s Students", "main": "Holidays That Reflect New York&#8217;s Students ", "content_kicker": "Editorial", "kicker": "Editorial"}, "_id": "54fa5e6038f0d852c169adaa", "word_count": "397", "multimedia": [{"height": 126, "url": "images/2015/03/07/opinion/07sat4WEB/07sat4WEB-thumbWide.jpg", "legacy": {"wideheight": "126", "wide": "images/2015/03/07/opinion/07sat4WEB/07sat4WEB-thumbWide.jpg", "widewidth": "190"}, "subtype": "wide", "width": 190, "type": "image"}, {"height": 422, "url": "images/2015/03/07/opinion/07sat4WEB/07sat4WEB-articleLarge.jpg", "legacy": {"xlarge": "images/2015/03/07/opinion/07sat4WEB/07sat4WEB-articleLarge.jpg", "xlargewidth": "600", "xlargeheight": "422"}, "subtype": "xlarge", "width": 600, "type": "image"}, {"height": 75, "url": "images/2015/03/07/opinion/07sat4WEB/07sat4WEB-thumbStandard.jpg", "legacy": {"thumbnail": "images/2015/03/07/opinion/07sat4WEB/07sat4WEB-thumbStandard.